<P>THe complaynt that good men haue made agaynst you is not to slaunder you but of purpose to haue you and your Family depend vpon the Lord &amp; his truth: &amp; not vpon <HI>HN.</HI> or a|ny, although they boast neuer so much of the spirite of God: of trouble and persecution you complayne, and yet for your part you are safe inough, as
