<DIV2 TYPE="part">
<PB REF="21">
<HEAD>Vitell.</HEAD>
<P>FOr which cause sake I am moued to make a short rehearsall, by what meanes the Lord of his good|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> me out of <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">hin<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> igno|rance, and also made manifest vnto me, the life &amp; saluation. More I haue r<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">cyted the names&punc; of two w<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">iter<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">, which haue w<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="3 letters">ten aga<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ist the most holy seruice of loue, and agaynst the Lords minister HN. &amp; also a part of their slaunderous reportes to the end that the louers of trueth might pray vnto the Lord, that he of his gracious goodnesse will geue those slaunderers vnderstanding that they might perc<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">iue and vnderstand their horrible blasphemy against the Lord and so humble themselues &amp; repent, for I thinke it is all out of ignoraunte blindnes whatsoeuer they haue done whereby they might finde grace at the hands of the Lord &amp;c.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 TYPE="part">
<HEAD>Aunswere.</HEAD>
<P>IT were more requisite that you would declare vnto vs, what was
<PB REF="21">
