that language, to the griefe of God his children. You further say, that I ne|uer councelled with the Lord, &amp; there|fore know nothing of his secreates.</P>
<P>You sat vpon your iudgement seat when you writ this: how know you that I neuer cou~elled with the Lord? to councell with God w&eacute;e may as we are taught, (that is,) in praying and hearing of his most holy word, which I hope in the Lord, that euer he will guide me with his holy spirite to doe, and performe all the dayes of my lyfe: as for your secret Reuelations, and Prophesyes, I am vtterly ignoraunt of, they are things proper to your Fa|milye, but not to the Church of Christ.</P>
